06/02/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Croatia fully backs Macedonia's EU integration efforts and is ready to share its experience regarding the membership process, Croatian chief negotiator with the EU Vladimir Drobnjak told Macedonian Deputy Prime Minister in charge of European Affairs Gabriela Konevska-Trajkovska. 
Meeting in Skopje on Monday (February 5th), Drobnjak stressed that the negotiations require an efficient administrative structure in place before they start. 
Konevska-Trajkovska told him that 35 working groups have been established, one for every chapter.
In other news, the Macedonian Interior Ministry announced on Tuesday that a suspected Serbian criminal -- identified only by the initials V.J. 
-- was arrested at the Tabanovce border crossing on Friday. 
Macedonian TV Sitel identifies him as Vladimir Jovanovic-Japanac, sought by Belgium for a series of crimes including abduction, forgery and armed robbery. 
He is also a suspect in the March 2003 assassination of Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic. 
(Vecer, MIA, A1 TV - 06/02/07; MIA, MRT, A1 TV - 05/02/07)
